                "name": "Narrow Flight",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "When airborne, kongamatos can fold their wings around their bodies to fit through tight spaces. While flying, kongamatos can fit through areas up to half their width without suffering the penalties to movement and Armor Class and on attack rolls usually incurred for squeezing."
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Piercing Beak",
                "ability_type": "Extraordinary",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex",
                "text": "A kongamato\u2019s beak is extremely hard and adept at breaking objects. When attempting to sunder an item, a kongamato\u2019s beak attack does double damage and is treated as if it were adamantine for the purposes of overcoming the object\u2019s hardness."
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "name": "Wailing Dive",
                "ability_type": "Supernatural",
                "ability_type_abbrev": "Su",
                "text": "When a kongamato makes a charge while flying or uses its Flyby Attack feat, the creature\u2019s body becomes infused with energy, causing its bite to do an extra +1d6 points of sonic damage on that attack."
            }
